neovim bind ideas

ctrl-enter -> open action menu, e.g., like ctrl-enter in opencode
<Leader><Leader> as a "ctrl-shift" kind of overload for less common actions

neovim keys to consider remapping

Z - backspace in normal mode - almost always use something else to delete stuff in normal mode

H & L - top / bottom of screen - rarely useful, prime home row keys

: - will remap to register-replace

m & M - will remap to "move"

- need to find an alt bind for setting marks

Rules for nvim plugin specs

Rules for nvim plugin specs
1. Every plugins/*.lua file is an interface module.
2. Every interface module must include at least one real plugin that justifies the file.
3. Built-in mappings may live in that file if they belong to the same interface.
4. Built-in mappings can live in init on whichever spec is the best conceptual owner.
5. Plugin-specific mappings should live on the corresponding plugin spec when possible.
6. Prefer keys for plugin entrypoints and init for built-in or interface glue mappings.

